Editor's Note:China and 14 other economies signed the Regional Comprehensive Economic Partnership (RCEP) on Sunday to form the world's largest free trade zone, marking a historic win for multilateralism that would help regional and global economies cope with the COVID-19 pandemic and the rising protectionism.

